review_blob: most probably one of the best beers Ive ever tasted, Ive tried Saranac beers before and its Summer and I was ready to be disappointed with another so so tryin to be an IPA beer but its not ...its a PILS but made with American Hops now on my all time fave list, so crisp so clean and all together far too easy to drink with just the perfect aftertaste of a slight but effective bitterness.
It was the packaging that threw me off I thought was purchasing something brewed in Scotland not under license and it ended up tasting like most of Sleemans beers which I dont care for.
